Instruction
public static class Instruction.ADD
extends java.lang.Object
implements Instruction

Adds two registers and writes to a third. The ADD instruction has two modes: register-based and immediate (see Instruction.ADDimm ). In register mode, the contents of two registers, sr1 and sr2, are added and written to a destination register (dr). The syntax of the command is 0001dddsss0xxttt, where sss, ttt, and ddd represent the three-bit register indexes sr1, sr2, and dr, respectively, and the xs represent "don't care" bits.
